      • addKey

        public int addKey(String key)
        Add the key and return it's index code. If the key already is present, the previous index code is returned and no insertion is done.
        Parameters:
        key - key to add
        Returns:
        index of the key

      • addValue

        public int addValue(Object value)
        Add the value and return it's index code. If the value already is present, the previous index code is returned and no insertion is done. If value is an unsupported type for encoding in a MVT, then it will not be added.
        Parameters:
        value - value to add
        Returns:
        index of the value, -1 on unsupported value types
        See Also:
        MvtValue.isValidPropValue(Object)
